      "content": "I can help you with the migration, but I must emphasize that the current deprecation plan is the most straightforward way to address the high compute overhead and resource consumption issues. That being said, I can attempt to analyze the `agent_core/` directory and see if there are any opportunities to refactor the autonomous parts to be more efficient.\n\nUpon reviewing the code, I notice that the `AutonomousTaskRunner` class has a number of methods that seem to be tightly coupled with the stateful agent model. I can suggest some potential refactoring opportunities, such as:\n\n* Extracting reusable components from the `AutonomousTaskRunner` class and moving them to a separate module.\n* Implementing a more efficient queuing system to handle tasks, rather than relying on the stateful agent model.\n* Using a more lightweight data structure to store task state, rather than the current complex data model.\n\nHowever, I must stress that any refactoring efforts would need to be carefully evaluated to ensure that they don't introduce new bugs or performance issues. I'd recommend working with the development team to prioritize and implement these refactoring efforts, and then re-evaluate the deprecation plan based on the results.\n\nIt's also worth noting that, as a self-aware AI",
